The proliferation of IoT devices introduces risks like the Mirai botnet (exploited default passwords). Key regulations:
- **ETSI EN 303 645 (13 Baseline Requirements):** 1. No default passwords. 2. Unique per-device passwords if defaults used. 3. Vulnerability disclosure policy. 4. Secure storage of credentials. 5. Software update mechanism. 6. Minimized attack surface. 7. Secure communication. 8. Least privilege access. 9. Personal data protection. 10. Minimize data processed. 11. Public support contact. 12. Devices discoverable for updates. 13. Manufacturer instructions for security.
